@startuml
participant "API Gateway" as API
participant "Lambda Reverse Proxy" as LRP
participant "EventBridge" as EB
participant "Lambda Functions" as LF
participant "ECS Microservices" as ECS
participant "SQS Queues" as SQS
participant "SNS Topics" as SNS
participant "DynamoDB" as DDB
participant "S3" as S3
participant "CloudWatch" as CW

API -> LRP: Route request
LRP -> ECS: Forward to appropriate microservice
ECS -> DDB: Read/Write data
ECS -> S3: Store/Retrieve files
ECS -> SQS: Send/Receive messages
ECS -> SNS: Publish events
SNS -> LF: Trigger Lambda function
SNS -> EB: Route events
EB -> LF: Trigger Lambda function
EB -> ECS: Trigger microservice action
LF -> DDB: Process data
LF -> S3: Process files
LF -> SQS: Send/Receive messages
ECS -> CW: Send logs and metrics
LF -> CW: Send logs and metrics
CW -> SNS: Trigger alarms
@enduml